		<td><b>What it would take to build a repro of Akira for the NES</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Greetings everyone,
<br />
<br />I am curious to find out what it takes to make a repro of Akira for the FC/NES. I had thought that since the mapper, 33, is a bit on the odd side or at least uncommon, it would be hard to do. Well, to my surprise it looks like a few individuals are gearing up towards making repros of Akira and for a quite a price it seems. So would anyone know what materials would be needed and how much it would cost to make roughly? Thanks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>tepples</b> [ Fri Dec 23, 2011 11:22 pm ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_033" class="postlink">The mapper</a> appears comparable in capability to <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/INES_Mapper_206" class="postlink">MIMIC-1</a>, the predecessor to MMC3. Perhaps the easiest way to repro this game would be to first hack it to MMC3, at which point the cost is the same as the cost to repro any other MMC3 game.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


